The paper deals with the complexity of fundamental operations on algebraic sets, specifically triangular sets in dimension zero. This falls under the scope of computational algebraic geometry, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science. The paper uses Las-Vegas algorithms and modular composition, which are common techniques in computational algebraic geometry. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SC (Symbolic Computation), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
